"'''7'''" is a song by [[Prince (musician)|Prince]] and [[The New Power Generation]], from the 1992 album (the "[[Love Symbol Album]]"). The 7" [[B-side]] was an acoustic version of "7." The [[12" single]] included several remixes of "7", as well as a non-album track called "'''2 Whom It May Concern'''". "7" also appeared on two [[compilation album]]s: ''[[The Hits 1]]'' in 1993, and ''[[Ultimate (Prince album)|Ultimate]]'', in 2006.
"7" features a sample of the 1967 [[Otis Redding]] and [[Carla Thomas]] duet, "[[Tramp (song)|Tramp]]".
